agreed to wage increases of 100 percent for government workers 
agreed to rehire a key labor leader who had been fired 
retracted a decree declaring the strike illegal 
promised not to retaliate against strikers 
agreed to drop efforts to repeal a job security law passed by 
the sandinistas 
agreed to further pay increases pegged to a basic market basket 
average of 53 items 
