one of europes major northsouth links 
has been closed down after authorities found a bridge section of it 
had sunk about two feet causing major traffic jams for thousands 
of summer vacationers 
the closure thursday of the kneissl bridge cut off a highway 
connecting west germany to austria a major route for vacationers 
it also shut down the train line between munich west germany and 
the austrian city of innsbruck 
police tried to reroute traffic during the peak holiday season 
but it only led to tieups on alternate routes many of which lead 
through small towns in austria 
experts said one of the bridge supports appeared to have been 
partially dislodged by the force of the inn river flowing 
underneath it they said repairs could take one year 
