evidence of damage as she drove through town 
martinique is a french overseas department of 336000 people 
and a popular tourist destination it is situated between the 
caribbean islands of dominique and st lucia 
martinique is the site of one of the most devastating volcanic 
eruptions in history on may 8 1902 mt pelle erupted and in 
less than 3 minutes annihilated the city of st pierre killing an 
estimated 30000 people 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude an earthquake of 5 on the richter scale can cause 
considerable damage while one measuring 6 can cause severe damage 
