foreign embassies allowed to leave their country they speculate 
that the exodus could be the harbinger of the demise of communism 
in their abandoned country 
hundreds more refugees arrived in italy by ship today 
i give communism in my country one or two years said kola 
a 36yearold construction worker who is housed together with the 
other refugees in a workers barracks on the outskirts of prague 
like others he declined to give his full name out of fear of 
possible reprisals against his family at home 
it was intolerable we all dreaded the isolation kola said 
in fairly fluent italian he was one of the few who spoke anything 
but albanian 
kola claimed he spent five years in jail for publicly 
criticizing the late albanian leader enver hoxha 
some people spent up to 40 years in jail for similar 
offenses he added 
during his 40 years of leadership hoxha steered his country 
into increasing isolation internationally and suppressed dissent to 
maintain absolute rule of the communists 
the countrys current leader ramiz alia who took over after 
