hydrogen escaped from atlantis extensive plumbing system the 
shuttles classified defense department flight in midjuly 
consequently was put on hold 
in late may a hydrogen leak was detected in columbia while the 
shuttle was being fueled for an astronomy mission columbia was 
returned to the hangar for repairs atlantis remains at the launch 
pad 
the leaks have prompted nasa to ground the threeshuttle fleet 
it was the first time the fleet has been grounded since shuttle 
challenger exploded in january 1986 killing seven crew members no 
shuttle flew for twoandahalf years after that 
rockwell international the shuttle builder has identified 
columbias leak in laboratory tests in california but has not yet 
found the source in the group of pipes and valves linking the 
orbiter with the external tank 
