fire raced through a storage area at a 
kerrmcgee corp plant destroying 100 tons of a fuel oxidizer used 
in the space shuttle and military rockets 
authorities credited a new storage system mandated after a 
disastrous blast at a neighboring plant two years ago with averting 
a more serious fire or explosion 
fire and company officials say 1065 tons of ammonium 
perchorlate was destroyed in the blaze late thursday damage was 
estimated at 200000 according to rick stater operations manager 
at the plant 
kerrmcgee produces about 1500 tons of ammonium perchlorate per 
month according to stater 
stater and fire officials credited new fire safety regulations 
with averting a disaster similar to one on may 4 1988 when an 
explosion of ammonium perchlorate destroyed the pacific engineering 
co pepcon plant a mile from the kerrmcgee facility 
kerrmcgee and pepcon were the only companies in the united 
states producing the critical fuel oxidizer and the loss of the 
pepcon plant left us officials faced with a possible shortage of 
the critical fuel element 
pepcon has since rebuilt a new plant in cedar city utah 
the pepcon blast killed two people and injured more than 300 
the blast rocked the las vegas valley and cause more than 74 
million in property damage primarily in this community of 55000 
some 25 miles southeast of las vegas 
following the pepcon blast clark county fire officials imposed 
strict new fire safety codes at the kerrmcgee plant included was 
a provision that ammonium perchlorate be stored on separate pads 
with concrete walls separating the pads 
