the roundtrip ride past the statue of liberty referred to by 
many as the best bargain in town is being doubled to 50 cents aug 
1 to ease the citys budget crunch 
despite protests from commuters in the citys least populated 
borough mayor david dinkins made it a done deal thursday when he 
signed the fare increase into law 
it is only the second official price hike in the history of the 
ferry which was taken over by the city from the bampo railroad in 
1905 
the ferry cost a nickel each way when edna st vincent millay 
wrote we were very tired we were very merry we had gone back 
and forth all night on the ferry 
but the famous nickel ride was fudged in 1972 when it became a 
10cent round trip collected in manhattan it was altogether 
obliterated when the fare went to a quarter in 1975 at the height 
of the citys fiscal troubles 
new fiscal woes have caused dinkins to raise the fare again the 
mayor facing a 18 billion deficit says the increase will add 2 
million to city coffers 
the staten island ferry which glides past but does not stop at 
the statue of liberty carries 30000 commuters daily and is one of 
the cheapest tourist attractions in new york 
