<TEXT>
more than 100 tons of a chemical that is 
vital for the solid fuel in space shuttle boosters went up in 
flames at a kerrmcgee corp plant near a similar plant that blew 
up two years ago 
no injuries were reported in thursday nights fire which was 
extinguished in about 45 minutes 
damage was originally estimated at 200000 but was revised 
downward friday to 135000 said kerrmcgee spokesman myron 
cunningham 
the cause of the accident was under investigation cunningham 
said 
the fire destroyed 1065 tons of ammonium perchlorate an 
oxidizer which provides oxygen for the burning of solid rocket 
fuel kerrmcgee produces about 1500 tons of the material per 
month according to rick stater plant operations manager 
stater and fire officials credited new fire safety regulations 
with averting a disaster similar to one on may 4 1988 when 
ammonium perchlorate exploded and destroyed the pacific engineering 
co or pepcon plant a mile from the kerrmcgee plant 
kerrmcgee and pacific engineering were the only companies in 
the united states producing the critical oxidizer which is also 
used for some military rockets and the loss of the plant left us 
officials facing a possible shortage 
pacific engineering since has built a new plant in cedar city 
utah 
the earlier blast killed two people and injured more than 300 
the blast rocked the las vegas valley and caused more than 74 
million in property damage primarily in this community of 55000 
some 25 miles southeast of las vegas 
following that blast clark county fire officials imposed strict 
new fire safety codes at the kerrmcgee plant included was a 
provision that the ammonium perchlorate not be stored in one pile 
but be divided up for storage on individual pads separated by 
concrete walls 
stater and fire department spokesman bob leinbach said the 
safety walls prevented the spread of the fire and possible 
explosion 
leinbach said he did not know why the kerrmcgee fire did not 
produce an explosion similar to the pacific engineering blast 
that may be one of the mysteries of life leinbach said 
pepcon was not supposed to explode 
kerrmcgee is building a new plant in a remote area northwest of 
las vegas for production of ammonium perchlorate 
