when a young sailor wrote a letter to his 
parents during the vietnam war he forgot to include the zip code 
that might have made it a little late but doesnt account for 
all 23 years the us postal service says 
bert budai wrote his parents a 2page letter filled with 
typical adventures of a young sailor during the war he returned 
home in 1969 and his parents later died 
but the post office delivered the letter tuesday to budais 
former home in ravenna just across the road from where he now 
lives 
i was quite shocked said budai now 44 married and 
stepfather of two children my sister lives in my fathers house 
now and it came to that address and she brought it over to me 
