passage to the cubans who had sought shelter earlier this week at 
pragues embassy in havana and said it would not hand them over to 
cuban authorities 
the cubans apparently followed the example of thousands of 
albanians who recently flooded foreign embassies in their capital 
tirana to seek asylum and received permission to leave their 
communist homeland 
cuba and albania remain among the last hardline communist 
countries in the world and have resisted the democratic reforms 
sweeping eastern europe and the soviet union 
