<TEXT>
mikhail s gorbachev closed the communist partys 
28th congress friday by saying he would welcome western aid without 
political strings and warning of a gap between the party and 
the people 
the congress elected a new 412member central committee that 
appeared to be packed with moderate reformers of the gorbachev 
mold and gorbachev ousted hardliner yegor k ligachev from the 
central committee and the politburo 
the nearly 4700 delegates to the congress closed their 
tumultuous twoweek session by giving themselves a standing ovation 
and singing the internationale the socialist anthem 
the congress was the stormiest in the kremlin since 1921 when 
bolshevik revolutionaries faced violent uprisings among workers and 
sailors 
it also marked a major political victory for gorbachev and 
cemented his hold over the party it will be a different party 
however with the exodus of maverick boris n yeltsin and other 
reformers 
the congress opened july 2 with a demand from a miner that 
gorbachev and the entire leadership resign the meeting hit its 
emotional peak on thursday when yeltsin announced his resignation 
from the 18million member organization 
at the close of the congress delegates applauded gorbachevs 
statement that this is the end of the cold war and that doors 
were opening to the west 
the decision of leaders of seven industrialized nations to 
consider offering the soviet union economic aid he said showed 
the success of his governments effort to overcome selfisolation 
and become an integral part of the world economy 
western leaders meeting this week in houston texas resolved 
to study giving economic aid to moscow as advocated by west 
germany and france 
president bush said wednesday he would look more favorably on 
helping the soviet government if it would cut defense spending 
gorbachev told delegates we are ready to cooperate and will 
be grateful for assistance being not just seekers but partners who 
are not going to take anything free 
i want to emphasize that i exclude all attempts to stipulate 
any political conditions for such cooperation gorbachev said 
it can and it must develop on an equal and mutually beneficial 
grounds 
his comments were the highestlevel soviet response to the 
houston summit 
in a surprise development the largely traditionalist party 
congress approved gorbachevs plan to nearly double the size of the 
politburo to 23 members and give seats to the party leaders of the 
15 soviet republics 
the central committee met late friday night to choose politburo 
members but no decision was made by early saturday the politburo 
the partys highest body was redesigned to ensure a moderate cast 
and help reduce the ethnic tension that is ripping the country 
apart 
restructuring the politburo also marked a triumph in gorbachevs 
drive to shift power from the party to the government which he 
also heads the politburo appeared unlikely to meet frequently or 
to seek control matters not dealing directly with the party 
gorbachev smiling relaxed and very much in control warned the 
delegates in his sixminute closing remarks of a gap between the 
party committees and workers peasants and intellectuals 
he denounced those who like yeltsin demand repentence from 
the party settling scores those who declare it even a criminal 
organization those who attempt by doing this to remove the party 
from the political life of the country 
gorbachev in an interview with cbs news said he didnt see 
anything frightening in the prospect of a multiparty system 
emerging in the soviet union 
summing up the results of the congress gorbachev said it did 
not mark as some thought the death of the party but rather the 
rebirth and renewal of the communist party 
in spite of all the criticism all the delegates feel 
certain that were on the right course and that reforms should 
advance in all directions he told cbs news 
yeltsins theatrical announcement that he was quitting the 
party and statements by other reformers that they two were 
leaving signaled the first split in the party since factions were 
formally banned in 1921 
besides yeltsin the reformist mayors of moscow and leningrad 
gavriil popov and anatoly sobchak also announced they were 
quitting the party along with leaders of the radical democratic 
platform 
equally worrisome from gorbachevs perspective was a nationwide 
warning strike wednesday by miners who demanded that 
nationalization of all party assets and a mass exodus of workers 
from the party 
yeltsin sobchak and popov have also indicated they would use 
their government positions to divest the party of its billions of 
rubles worth of publishing houses office buildings cars and 
vacation resorts 
thousands of people have quit the party in recent months and 
the departure of the reform leaders and the rising anger of miners 
and other workers appeared likely to accelerate that process the 
precise impact could not immediately be determined although it 
cracked the unity among reformers that gorbachev has been urging 
