economy the kind of boost the white house wants to bolster 
republican chances in the november congressional elections a 
change in monetary policy can take as long as six months to ripple 
through the economy 
jones said he expects the fed to cut rates by late july 
virtually announcing the move in advance allows greenspan to focus 
attention on the reasons he prefers to highlight and shift 
attention from other reasons he said 
the fed wants to link this easing to the credit crunch and not 
to any political factors he said 
