<TEXT>
bond prices posted another broad advance friday 
as the federal reserve took steps that traders viewed as evidence 
the central bank was adopting a more generous credit policy 
a day after federal reserve chairman alan greenspan hinted that 
the fed was poised to relax credit conditions because loans were 
becoming harder to get the central bank injected reserves into the 
banking system at midday 
the move led to a quarterpoint decline in a key lending rate 
the treasurys benchmark 30year bond climbed 1732 point or 
about 525 per 1000 face amount after rising 750 on thursday 
its yield which falls when prices rise dropped to 845 percent 
from 849 percent late thursday 
bond prices moved higher from the start of trading on 
expectations that interest rates would be moving lower in the wake 
of greenspans comments thursday to the senate banking committee 
prices moved even higher in late morning trading when the fed 
added reserves to the banking system by arranging shortterm 
purchases of securities 
with more funds available to banks the federal funds rate 
which is the interest that banks charge each other for shortterm 
loans slipped to 8 percent from 8 percent late thursday the 
funds rate had fluctuated near 8 percent for months 
the fed eased said maria fiorini ramirez who heads a 
consulting firm that bears her name they are putting greenspans 
may and might into action 
the federal funds rate is often seen as an indicator of which 
way other lending rates are headed 
but mrs ramirez said she does not expect a quick decline in 
consumer lending rates to follow the move in the federal funds rate 
because many banks are facing profit pressures due to shaky real 
estate and third world loans 
meanwhile government reports on wholesale inflation and retail 
sales went virtually ignored by bond traders 
the commerce department said declining food and energy prices 
helped hold the producer price index to a modest 02 percent in 
june however costs of other items were up more sharply than in 
recent months 
a separate report showed retail sales rose 05 percent in june 
snapping a string of five straight monthly declines 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
governments rose 732 point intermediate maturities gained between 
point and 1332 point and longterm issues advanced as much as 
1732 point according to telerate inc a financial information 
service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer rose 310 to 116196 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds rose 732 point to 92rsqb the average yield to 
maturity slipped to 742 percent from 744 percent late thursday 
yields on threemonth treasury bills fell to 783 percent as the 
discount dropped 8 basis points to 759 percent yields on 
sixmonth bills fell to 789 percent as the discount declined 7 
basis points to 750 percent yields on oneyear bills fell to 789 
percent as the discount fell 7 basis points to 736 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
